    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. BRAT:H.R. 937.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:The Sixteenth Amendment to the Constitution grants Congress``power to lay and collect taxes on incomes, from whateversource derived, without apportionment among the severalStates, and without regard to any census or enumeration.''Left undefined in the amendment, the ``incomes'' appropriatefor taxation must be determined through legislation passed byCongress. Congress therefore has the power to exclude fromincome taxation such sources as it deems appropriate.[Page H1085]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
